---
title: Chana Masala with Brown Rice and Cucumber Raita
description: Chana Masala is a dish eaten in most parts of India from Delhi in the North to Chennai in the South. 'Chana' means chickpea and 'masala' means spice mix, so while in different parts of India, the Chana Masala can have its very own personality and quirks, it will always be fragrant and 100% delicious.
